TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">a</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Eclips, can you tell more about the technique you use against the Giants please?  I would really like to try it out sometime  =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Seik Stormreaver</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Heh.... This ain't Elips, but I know how he does it. It's kinda hard at first (I know... I've done it), but it goes a little something like this :<BR>1) Find your target, and get a distance ahead of it.<BR>2)Use the bellows song, once it hits, start running forward. Repeatedly use the bellows song until it falls.<BR>3) If your target is almost close enough to hit you, switch to Selo's and get ahead a bit.<BR>4) Sometime monsters can run faster than your regular run, requiring you to keep Selo's up almost the entire time. Just use 1 pulse of Selo's, then 2 bellows.<P><BR>Hope that was accurate, and that you can use it =)<P>                          Seik Stormreaver<BR>                        Bard of his 27th song</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">a</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I was thinking maybe Eclips used charm on one and killed the other using it then would fear and chain the other to kill it...or some such</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Wondering Bard</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Well, Theoretically you could do it Seik's way...but against a HG, kiting it with bellow and selo's would take an *extremely* long time, the way Eclips is saying he does it, he charms one, makes it attack the other, by the time one is killed, the one that he had charmed is almost dead due to the beating it took in battle, then he can use the fear song, and beat it while it tries to run away, Therefore solo'ing 2 at once. But you have to be careful, because the charm song only lasts around 10-15 seconds, if you aren't careful, you will have two very angry HG's on you, and they will kill you extremely fast.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Faldyyen Thunderleaf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Do bards have the same 6lvl resistance cap that the casters have?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Cirdan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Yes Unfourtunatly we cannot charm a creature above lvl 37, same cap applies. Its pretty dumb.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Eclips Solar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">heh cool, didn't think this post would still be on...<P>no, I didn't use that horrible long kiting with the boastfull bellow, that would take me half an hour per giant or so, and I said it would take me less than 10 minutes to put 2 giants under the ground...<P>Battle Plan:<BR>-be sure to have all yer charisma stuff on (this is crude stein incl.), dont attempt with a charisma below 140-150<BR>-travel to Rathe Mountains <BR>-find a nice and calm place amongst the giants...<BR>-Target giant nr1 <BR>-Charm him (DON'T FORGET TO RECHARM EVERY FEW SECONDS)<BR>-/pet kill on second giant<BR>-watch the 2 meanies bonk eachother on the head<BR>-before the end of the battle check which giant has the highest HP, be sure to have him charmed<BR>-when one giant bites the dust(you gain experience), consonant chain the charmed one asap when he regains his lust to squish you.<BR>-take out that second (ugh) ykesha<BR>-scream like hell<BR>-rip open the back of the slowly fleeing giant.<BR>-you gain exp<BR>-loot the 2 corpses, if yer lucky yer bout 80pp richer  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/smile.gif"><P>Eclips Solar<BR>extremely happy bard of 41 songs </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">a</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FAC